  <thing id="c5CPthWolf" name="Path of the Wolfsblood" description="All barbarians must learn to master their rage; the Wolfsblood are those whose wrath stems from an inborn or inflicted lycanthropic curse. Through this path of training, noble Wolfsbloods turn this evil power to their advantage, while the worst follow in their ancestors’ bloody footsteps. Only those who have taken on the curse of lycanthropy may adopt this path; it is most commonly passed on from another Wolfsblood in a blood-soaked rite of passage.\n\nOther types of lycanthropic barbarians are found in legend, such as the Bear-kin, the Boarblood, and the Black Stripes. If any of them still\nremain, they follow their own traditions. \n\nThe saving throw DC for your Moonstruck and Cursed Bite abilities is 8 + your Constitution modifier + your proficiency bonus. The restriction\nagainst concentrating on spells while raging does not apply to your Moonstruck or Cursed Bite features." compset="CustomSpec" uniqueness="unique">
